    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ceiling ribs that are partly or entirely detached from the surface of the vault, thus without vaulting cells and forming an aerial network; found in German and English Late Gothic architecture. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor plafondribben die gedeeltelijk of geheel losstaan van het gewelfoppervlak, dus zonder gewelfscellen, waardoor ze een luchtig netwerk vormen. Wordt aangetroffen in Duitse en Engelse laat-gotische architectuur.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>與拱頂表面部分或完全分離的屋頂肋條，故不含拱頂隔間並形成架空網絡，常見於德國或英國的歌德式晚期建築。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>As nervuras do teto são parcial ou totalmente destacadas da superfície da abóbada,  formando uma rede aérea; encontradas na arquitetura gótica tardia alemã e inglesa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
